\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {3.1}{\ignorespaces Use case diagram for TruthfulRAG v5. The primary actor (\emph {User}) initiates four interactions. \emph {Ollama LLM} (secondary actor) handles schema inference and answer generation; \emph {Neo4j} handles graph storage and retrieval. Dashed arrows show \textit {include} (mandatory sub-step) and \textit {extend} (optional enrichment) relationships.}}{10}{figure.caption.9}%
\addvspace {10\p@ }
\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {4.1}{\ignorespaces Six-layer pipeline architecture of TruthfulRAG v5.}}{14}{figure.caption.11}%
\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {4.2}{\ignorespaces End-to-end pipeline flow of TruthfulRAG v5 (landscape view). Eight stages — \emph {Corpus Ingestion} [A1/N1/N4/N5], \emph {Hybrid Retrieval} [BM25+Semantic], \emph {Query Processing} [B4/C7], \emph {Scoring} [N2], \emph {Conflict Resolution} [SAFE\_FOR elimination], \emph {Adaptive Entropy Filter} [auto-keep], \emph {Confidence Calculation}, and \emph {Final Answer} — are shown with their decision logic and inter-stage data flows. Function identifiers in brackets correspond to the implementation in Chapter~5.}}{16}{figure.caption.12}%
\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {4.3}{\ignorespaces Property graph model for TruthfulRAG v5 (the graph-database equivalent of an ER diagram). \emph {Top}: Schema — one node type \texttt {:Entity} with properties \texttt {name} and \texttt {type}; one relationship type \texttt {RELATED\_TO} carrying the five properties used for scoring and conflict resolution. \emph {Bottom}: Two instance edges from the medical corpus showing the conflicting aspirin facts that the v5 conflict resolver must adjudicate.}}{17}{figure.caption.13}%
\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {4.4}{\ignorespaces Deployment architecture of TruthfulRAG v5. All three components --- the core pipeline, the graph database, and the language model --- run on the same machine with no external network connections. No user data leaves the host at any point.}}{18}{figure.caption.14}%
\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {4.5}{\ignorespaces Activity diagram for query processing in TruthfulRAG v5. The conflict-resolution branch (left) loops back until all contradicting facts are resolved before the surviving evidence is assembled into the final prompt.}}{19}{figure.caption.15}%
\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {4.6}{\ignorespaces State transition diagram for TruthfulRAG v5. Normal execution cycles: \textsc {Idle} $\to $ \textsc {Ingesting} $\to $ \textsc {Ready} $\to $ \textsc {Retrieving} $\to $ \textsc {Resolving} $\to $ \textsc {Generating} $\to $ \textsc {Ready}. Any runtime error transitions the system to \textsc {Error}; a process restart resets it to \textsc {Idle}.}}{20}{figure.caption.16}%
\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {4.7}{\ignorespaces Level-0 Context DFD for TruthfulRAG v5. The circle is the complete system; rectangles are external entities. Solid arrows = inputs; dashed = outputs.}}{22}{figure.caption.17}%
\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {4.8}{\ignorespaces Level-1 DFD: the four internal sub-processes of TruthfulRAG v5 and their external service interactions. Each row is fully independent; solid arrows are requests, dashed arrows are responses.}}{23}{figure.caption.18}%
\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {4.9}{\ignorespaces End-to-end sequence diagram for corpus load and query}}{25}{figure.caption.19}%
